[[File:Esb_repulsorlift_carbonite.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[Han Solo]]'s [[Carbonite|frozen]] form is carried by repulsorlift]]
{{Quote|Its powered repulsors and the sails made from the leaves of our giant trees help us to ride the winds of the planet.|[[Rix Tegano]] introducing the [[Jedi Initiate]]s to the [[sky skimming board]]|<ref name="The Great Leaf Glide">{{YJA|The Great Leaf Glide}}</ref>}}
'''Repulsorlift''',<ref name="ICS">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref> also known as '''repulsor''',<ref name="The Great Leaf Glide" /> was a technology that allowed a craft to hover or even fly over a [[planet]]'s surface by pushing against its [[gravity]], producing thrust.<ref name="ICS">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: Incredible Cross-Sections]]''</ref> Repulsorlift engines or "[[antigrav]]s" created fields of negative gravity called "[[repulsor field]]s" which pushed against a planet's natural gravitational field.<ref name="CFOWM">''[[YT-1300 Millennium Falcon Owners' Workshop Manual]]''</ref>

Vehicles that utilized the repulsorlift technology as their primary method of propulsion, including [[speeder bike]]s, were known as [[repulsorcraft]]s.<ref name="ICS" /> [[Bakur Repulsor Corporation]] was one such manufacturer of the engines,<ref name="BMF 38">{{BuildFalconCite|38|Secrets of Spaceflight}}</ref> while [[Aratech Repulsor Company]] was a manufacturer of craft that utilized this technology.<ref name="databank Ezra">{{Databank|ezras-speeder-bike|Ezra's Speeder Bike}}</ref> Vehicles that used repulsorlift technology included the [[Gian heavy patrol speeder]],<ref name="Databank Gian speeder">{{Databank|gian-speeder|Gian Speeder}}</ref> the [[Single Trooper Aerial Platform]] (STAP),<ref name="Databank">{{Databank|stap|STAP}}</ref> the [[Flash speeder]],<ref name="Databank Flash speeder">{{Databank|flash-speeder|Flash Speeder}}</ref> the [[Armored Assault Tank Mk I|AAT Battle Tank]],<ref name="Databank AAT">{{Databank|aat-battle-tank|AAT Battle Tank}}</ref> and the [[LAAT/le patrol gunship|patrol transports]].<ref name="policegunship">{{Databank|patrol-transport|Patrol Transport}}</ref>

On [[starship]]s, repulsorlift engines were a secondary form of propulsion, used for atmospheric flight and docking procedures. On many ships like the [[YT-1300 light freighter]] there was a dedicated [[fusion generator]] to power the repulsorlifts,<ref name="CFOWM" /> though smaller ships like the [[X-wing starfighter|X-wing]] [[starfighter]] drew energy from the [[sublight engine]]s to power their repulsorlifts.<ref name="RSOWM">''[[Rebel Starfighters Owners' Workshop Manual]]''</ref>

Repulsorlift technology could be used in everyday items such as [[Repulsorlift chair|chairs]]<ref name="DB Agruss">{{Databank|keeper-agruss|Keeper Agruss}}</ref> and [[Repulsorpod|speaking platforms]].<ref name="SWAEYNTK">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref> It was also possible to weaponize repulsor technology to create shockwaves capable of repelling enemies in a similar manner to a [[Force push]], notably being used by [[Mandalorian warrior]]s who have specialized [[Mandalorian vambrace|vambraces]],<ref name="Trials of the Darksaber">{{Rebels|Trials of the Darksaber}}</ref> [[clone commando]]s,<ref name="Battlefront II"> ''[[Star Wars Battlefront II]]''</ref> and the [[Haxion Brood]]'s [[bounty hunter]]s.<ref name="Jedi Fallen Order">''[[Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order]]''</ref>

